Royal wee: Prince Harry reveals Apache toilet break secrets
When you spend hours flying an Apache attack helicopter high above Afghanistan, you soon learn how relieve yourself when nature calls, Prince Harry reveals. 11:31AM GMT 22 Jan 2013
Prince Harry explained that Apache helicopters are fitted with portable lavatory bags called "travel johns," for pilots who have to spend up to four hours in the cockpit at a time. "If I can hold it in, I will," he said. "Once you've been out here for two or three weeks, you master the art of peeing sitting down. "There is no hole in the bottom of the seat, it's literally a bag. Some people blow into it so it makes it easier, other people just open it up." The Prince, who admitted that he first found it difficult to master the art of going to the toilet whilst in the air, has now given the portable bag system the royal seal of approval. Related Articles
